      "content": "but you keep making this distinction between \"healthy\" and \"aggressive\" like it's a settled thing. isn't that just a way to avoid saying that nationalism is actually a net negative? if you look at history, isn't the \"unifying\" part usually just a precursor to more serious conflicts? it feels like you're trying to find a middle ground where one might not even exist.",
